<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> Mastering Audio: The Art and the Science by <a href="/wiki/Bob_Katz" title="Bob Katz">Bob Katz</a>, pages 49-50, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780240805450" class="internal">ISBN 978-0-24-080545-0</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9" title="">^</a></b> 6-Bit vs. 8-Bit....PVA/MVA vs. TN+Film Are Things Changing? <a href="http://www.tftcentral.co.uk/articles/6bit_8bit.htm" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.tftcentral.co.uk/articles/6bit_8bit.htm" rel="nofollow">[1]</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-dhalf-10">^ <a href="#cite_ref-dhalf_10-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-dhalf_10-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-dhalf_10-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-dhalf_10-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFCrockerBoulay.2C_Paul_.26_Morra.2C_Mike"><a href="/wiki/Lee_Daniel_Crocker" title="Lee Daniel Crocker">Crocker, Lee Daniel</a>; Boulay, Paul &amp; Morra, Mike (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1991-06-20"><a href="/wiki/1991" title="1991">1991</a>-<a href="/wiki/June_20" title="June 20">06-20</a></span>). <a href="http://www.efg2.com/Lab/Library/ImageProcessing/DHALF.TXT" class="external text" title="http://www.efg2.com/Lab/Library/ImageProcessing/DHALF.TXT" rel="nofollow">"Digital Halftoning"</a>. <i>Computer Lab and Reference Library</i><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.efg2.com/Lab/Library/ImageProcessing/DHALF.TXT" class="external free" title="http://www.efg2.com/Lab/Library/ImageProcessing/DHALF.TXT" rel="nofollow">http://www.efg2.com/Lab/Library/ImageProcessing/DHALF.TXT</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-09-10</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Digital+Halftoning&amp;rft.atitle=Computer+Lab+and+Reference+Library&amp;rft.aulast=Crocker&amp;rft.aufirst=Lee+Daniel&amp;rft.au=Crocker%2C+Lee+Daniel&amp;rft.au=Boulay%2C+Paul+%26+Morra%2C+Mike&amp;rft.date=%5B%5B1991-06-20%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.efg2.com%2FLab%2FLibrary%2FImageProcessing%2FDHALF.TXT&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Dither"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> <i>Note: this article contains a minor mistake: “(To fully reproduce our 256-level image, we would need to use an</i> <b>8x8</b> <i>pattern.)” The bold part should read “16x16”.</i></li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFSilvaLucena.2C_Paula_Salgado_.26_Figuerola.2C_Wilfredo_Blanco">Silva, Aristófanes Correia; Lucena, Paula Salgado &amp; Figuerola, Wilfredo Blanco (<span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2000-12-13"><a href="/wiki/2000" title="2000">2000</a>-<a href="/wiki/December_13" title="December 13">12-13</a></span>). <a href="http://www.visgraf.impa.br/Courses/ip00/proj/Dithering1/" class="external text" title="http://www.visgraf.impa.br/Courses/ip00/proj/Dithering1/" rel="nofollow">"Average Dithering"</a>. <i>Image Based Artistic Dithering</i>. Visgraf Lab<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.visgraf.impa.br/Courses/ip00/proj/Dithering1/" class="external free" title="http://www.visgraf.impa.br/Courses/ip00/proj/Dithering1/" rel="nofollow">http://www.visgraf.impa.br/Courses/ip00/proj/Dithering1/</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2007-09-10</span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Average+Dithering&amp;rft.atitle=Image+Based+Artistic+Dithering&amp;rft.aulast=Silva&amp;rft.aufirst=Arist%C3%B3fanes+Correia&amp;rft.au=Silva%2C+Arist%C3%B3fanes+Correia&amp;rft.au=Lucena%2C+Paula+Salgado+%26+Figuerola%2C+Wilfredo+Blanco&amp;rft.date=%5B%5B2000-12-13%5D%5D&amp;rft.pub=Visgraf+Lab&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.visgraf.impa.br%2FCourses%2Fip00%2Fproj%2FDithering1%2F&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Dither"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-12" title="">^</a></b> See <a href="/wiki/Color_quantization" title="Color quantization">color quantization</a> for a description of Spatial color quantization algorithm (scolorq). The website which describes it in more detail is at <a href="http://www.moonflare.com/code/scolorq/" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.moonflare.com/code/scolorq/" rel="nofollow">[2]</a>.</li>
<li id="cite_note-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-13" title="">^</a></b> Imagemagick source code, file magick/quantize.c, and online manual which mentions the dithering method by name: <a href="http://www.imagemagick.org/script/command-line-options.php" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.imagemagick.org/script/command-line-options.php" rel="nofollow">[3]</a></li>
</ol>
<p>More recent research in the field of dither for audio was done by Lipshitz, Vanderkooy, and Wannamaker at the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Waterloo" title="University of Waterloo">University of Waterloo</a>.<a href="http://audiolab.uwaterloo.ca/stan.htm" class="external autonumber" title="http://audiolab.uwaterloo.ca/stan.htm" rel="nofollow">[6]</a></p>
